1
00:00:04,671 --> 00:00:05,900
<i>Previously on</i> ER:

2
00:00:06,073 --> 00:00:07,371
If we're gonna do this...

3
00:00:07,541 --> 00:00:09,100
we have to do this together.

4
00:00:09,276 --> 00:00:11,541
Remembering a dream I
had last night. Sam was in it.

5
00:00:11,712 --> 00:00:13,681
- I don't beg.
- In my dream you did.

6
00:00:13,847 --> 00:00:15,440
- This is Ortho.
- I start today.

7
00:00:15,616 --> 00:00:18,916
Dr. Rasgotra, I'd like you to
meet doctors Ramsey, Craig.

8
00:00:19,086 --> 00:00:20,430
Heard great things about you.

9
00:00:20,454 --> 00:00:22,432
What position did you play?
- Center forward.

10
00:00:22,456 --> 00:00:25,858
Love, trust, truth,
higher power.

11
00:00:26,026 --> 00:00:28,962
You can't have any of those
without faith. Especially love.

12
00:00:29,129 --> 00:00:31,621
No, this is your office.

13
00:00:34,902 --> 00:00:35,926
Nice desk.

14
00:00:41,642 --> 00:00:44,544
Ah. Imagine waking
up here every morning.

15
00:00:44,745 --> 00:00:48,307
- Bettina, I can't afford this.
- Yes, you can. I did the math.

16
00:00:49,650 --> 00:00:50,845
- You did the math?
- Mm-hm.

17
00:00:51,018 --> 00:00:55,149
Time to move out of your med school
apartment and invest in something.

18
00:00:55,355 --> 00:00:56,755
My apartment is fine.

19
00:00:56,957 --> 00:00:59,324
- So, what do you think?
- Oh, it's beautiful.

20
00:00:59,493 --> 00:01:03,897
Told you. The sellers did a
great job on the renovation.

21
00:01:04,064 --> 00:01:07,034
The kitchen, the moldings,
these yummy floors.

22
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:09,066
Bamboo flown in from Brazil.

23
00:01:09,269 --> 00:01:12,398
And there's a gym and a children's
game room in the basement.

24
00:01:12,573 --> 00:01:13,666
You two got kids?

25
00:01:13,874 --> 00:01:14,967
- No.
- No.

26
00:01:15,142 --> 00:01:16,542
Listen, don't rush it.

27
00:01:16,710 --> 00:01:20,147
When you're newlyweds and it's
just the two of you against the world...

28
00:01:20,314 --> 00:01:22,476
well, you can't beat that.

29
00:01:23,417 --> 00:01:24,817
Okay.

30
00:01:24,985 --> 00:01:28,717
It'll be gone by the end of the
week, so if you're at all interested...

31
00:01:28,889 --> 00:01:29,982
make an offer.

32
00:01:30,157 --> 00:01:31,887
No, thanks.

33
00:01:32,059 --> 00:01:35,427
- It's, uh, the first place he's seen.
- Think about it.

34
00:01:35,662 --> 00:01:39,656
- I'll call you tomorrow.
- No, don't, please.

35
00:01:39,833 --> 00:01:41,859
I'm just looking.

36
00:01:43,303 --> 00:01:44,999
Hey, Sam.

37
00:01:45,172 --> 00:01:47,732
- It wasn't just the battery.
- Where'd you get my keys?

38
00:01:47,908 --> 00:01:51,242
- You also had alternator issues.
- You stole my keys and fixed my car?

39
00:01:51,411 --> 00:01:54,108
I think the proper response
would be, "Thank you, Tony."

40
00:01:54,314 --> 00:01:56,783
Also, I tightened the connections
and got you all charged up.

41
00:01:56,950 --> 00:01:59,249
Ooh. That sounds like fun.

42
00:01:59,419 --> 00:02:02,583
- Thought you were dating the chaplain.
- He's talking about my car.

43
00:02:02,756 --> 00:02:03,849
Car.

44
00:02:04,024 --> 00:02:06,789
She made a reasonable
assumption about our relationship...

45
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:08,189
and you had a seizure.

46
00:02:08,362 --> 00:02:10,729
I wasn't feeling the
realtor. I wanted to get out.

47
00:02:10,897 --> 00:02:13,890
We're adults. The topic of
commitment shouldn't be off-limits.

48
00:02:14,067 --> 00:02:15,467
- It's not off-limits.
- Really?

49
00:02:15,636 --> 00:02:17,901
You haven't looked me
in the eye since we left.

50
00:02:18,071 --> 00:02:21,132
Come on, it's not like that.
- Pratt.

51
00:02:21,341 --> 00:02:25,142
Hey, Pratt. There's a kid and an old
guy who've been pulled out of the lake.

52
00:02:25,345 --> 00:02:27,246
- Take one with Grady.
- You got it.

53
00:02:27,414 --> 00:02:29,076
Let's talk about
this later, okay?

54
00:02:29,249 --> 00:02:31,582
You're admitting there's
something to talk about.

55
00:02:31,752 --> 00:02:33,778
- Hey, Chaz, how you doing?
- Fine, thanks.

56
00:02:33,954 --> 00:02:35,047
What up?

57
00:02:35,222 --> 00:02:38,283
Robert Truman, 68. Jumped in
after a kid who fell into the lake.

58
00:02:38,458 --> 00:02:40,450
Thought I could get
in and out. Too cold.

59
00:02:40,627 --> 00:02:42,721
Heart rate's 68, pulse
ox good. Temp was 90.

60
00:02:42,896 --> 00:02:45,889
- My lungs froze up, couldn't swim.
- Does anything hurt, sir?

61
00:02:46,099 --> 00:02:48,830
I'm fine. Take care of the boy.
- Barely moving air.

62
00:02:49,002 --> 00:02:51,995
- Too cold, can't get a sat.
- Twenty-four gauge PIV, that's it?

63
00:02:52,172 --> 00:02:54,573
- He needs central access.
- Mom is here. It's okay.

64
00:02:54,741 --> 00:02:56,801
This is your fault.
You made this happen.

65
00:02:56,977 --> 00:02:59,412
He needed my help. I
thought if I could only do...

66
00:02:59,613 --> 00:03:01,741
Why won't you leave us alone?

67
00:03:01,948 --> 00:03:05,112
- No, I'm sorry, I tried to...
- Stay away from my son.

68
00:03:05,318 --> 00:03:07,480
- He's hypoventilating.
- We need to bag him.

69
00:03:07,654 --> 00:03:11,250
- Doctor, please take care of that child.
- We're gonna concentrate on you now.

70
00:03:11,425 --> 00:03:13,690
If you wanna help me,
you need to help that boy.

71
00:03:13,894 --> 00:03:15,487
- Mr. Truman...
- Please save him.

72
00:03:15,662 --> 00:03:18,598
Save him or I'm going to hell.

73
00:03:27,841 --> 00:03:30,834
The nurse wants to bump our
meniscus repair until tomorrow.

74
00:03:31,011 --> 00:03:33,503
Tell her to kiss your ass,
or maybe mine. She's cute.

75
00:03:33,714 --> 00:03:36,411
- What's up, Ortho girl?
- Morris, what are you doing here?

76
00:03:36,583 --> 00:03:38,518
- I'm a surgeon for the day.
- What?

77
00:03:38,719 --> 00:03:41,154
Yep, it's the ER's new
trauma-exchange program.

78
00:03:41,321 --> 00:03:44,587
- I never heard anything about this.
- ER staff can spend a day...

79
00:03:44,758 --> 00:03:46,624
following trauma
patients to the O.R.

80
00:03:46,793 --> 00:03:48,625
- You gonna scrub in on cases?
- Hope so.

81
00:03:48,795 --> 00:03:51,094
Be good and Harold might
let you hold his retractor.

82
00:03:51,264 --> 00:03:52,698
Definitely. MORRIS: Ha-ha.

83
00:03:52,866 --> 00:03:56,325
Dude, I gotta go. There's
like a hundred doctors here.

84
00:03:56,937 --> 00:03:58,997
- After you.
- No, after you.

85
00:03:59,239 --> 00:04:00,798
Rasgotra, you're up.

86
00:04:00,974 --> 00:04:04,138
Silas is our snowmobile versus
brick wall. Post op day one...

87
00:04:04,344 --> 00:04:06,006
She's so cute, isn't she?

88
00:04:06,546 --> 00:04:09,106
- Day one from laparotomy...
- With her little accent.

89
00:04:10,884 --> 00:04:12,443
Hemoglobin's stable, slept well.

90
00:04:12,619 --> 00:04:16,021
Got a chest x-ray. No infiltrates.
Mild atelectasis bilaterally.

91
00:04:16,189 --> 00:04:19,216
- Okay.
- That means areas of collapsed alveoli.

92
00:04:19,392 --> 00:04:20,792
We know what atelectasis is.

93
00:04:20,961 --> 00:04:24,022
It's probably nothing, but I can
repeat the film this afternoon.

94
00:04:24,197 --> 00:04:25,290
Okay.

95
00:04:25,465 --> 00:04:28,060
Hey, what's the definition
of a double-blind study?

96
00:04:28,268 --> 00:04:31,170
- Two ortho docs looking at a chest film.
- Zing.

97
00:04:32,539 --> 00:04:35,202
Don't pretend that's not
funny. You taught me that joke.

98
00:04:35,375 --> 00:04:38,277
Oh, my God, I love this girl.

99
00:04:39,212 --> 00:04:42,341
He was collecting samples
from the lake for a science project.

100
00:04:42,516 --> 00:04:46,715
- Something about algae in winter.
- Core temp's 74.3.

101
00:04:46,887 --> 00:04:48,378
More suction, please.

102
00:04:48,555 --> 00:04:50,854
Then that man just appears
out of nowhere again.

103
00:04:51,024 --> 00:04:52,048
Tube.

104
00:04:52,225 --> 00:04:55,024
He's been to the store,
trying to talk to me while I work.

105
00:04:55,228 --> 00:04:57,424
I thought he was just
some lonely old guy.

106
00:04:57,597 --> 00:05:00,396
And yesterday, I saw
him outside of my house.

107
00:05:00,567 --> 00:05:02,900
Then when he saw me
looking, he just walked away.

108
00:05:03,436 --> 00:05:05,166
And then today at the lake...

109
00:05:05,372 --> 00:05:07,341
I went there to tell
him to stay away.

110
00:05:07,507 --> 00:05:10,067
I told him I was
gonna call the police.

111
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:13,178
Gabriel must have slipped
in while my back was turned.

112
00:05:13,346 --> 00:05:15,941
I have no idea how long he
was there before I realized.

113
00:05:16,183 --> 00:05:17,583
That man jumped in after him?

114
00:05:17,751 --> 00:05:19,913
He said, "Call 911,"
and then he just jumped.

115
00:05:20,086 --> 00:05:23,579
Sam, call Respiratory for a vent
and set up for bilateral chest tubes.

116
00:05:23,757 --> 00:05:26,352
Have Central bring in a
circulating-water blanket.

117
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:28,859
- He'll do better with a Bair Hugger.
- Both work.

118
00:05:29,062 --> 00:05:31,293
- Bair Hugger's better.
- Show me the data.

119
00:05:31,464 --> 00:05:33,933
You kids work it out.

120
00:05:34,134 --> 00:05:35,466
You guys all right in here?

121
00:05:35,635 --> 00:05:39,402
Yeah, his core temp's up to 94, but
his EKG shows ischemic changes.

122
00:05:39,573 --> 00:05:42,907
Could have been caused
by the strain of the cold swim.

123
00:05:43,109 --> 00:05:45,101
- Hey.
- These flattened T waves.

124
00:05:45,278 --> 00:05:48,908
I've had those for years.
It's definitely not an MI.

125
00:05:49,115 --> 00:05:52,984
I'm a doctor. Retired six years,
but I can still read an EKG.

126
00:05:53,153 --> 00:05:55,782
Okay, well, let us check
your troponins just in case.

127
00:05:55,989 --> 00:05:58,652
- Yeah, just knock yourself out.
- Where'd you practice?

128
00:05:58,859 --> 00:06:00,623
Stateville, 12 years.

129
00:06:01,228 --> 00:06:03,163
- Stateville Penitentiary?
- Yes.

130
00:06:03,363 --> 00:06:05,332
Bet that was intense.
You guys seem fine.

131
00:06:05,498 --> 00:06:07,899
- I'm going back in with the kid.
- How is he?

132
00:06:08,802 --> 00:06:12,102
- I can't talk about his treatment.
- Of course.

133
00:06:12,806 --> 00:06:14,832
Hey. Fun rounding
with you this morning.

134
00:06:15,008 --> 00:06:16,476
- Hi, Archie.
- Want some advice?

135
00:06:16,643 --> 00:06:19,408
- No.
- You need to work on your style.

136
00:06:19,579 --> 00:06:21,343
- Excuse me?
- Yeah, you're too serious.

137
00:06:21,514 --> 00:06:23,312
Have fun, take
some joy in your work.

138
00:06:23,483 --> 00:06:24,951
- I'm fun.
- You're English.

139
00:06:25,118 --> 00:06:28,316
I get it. It's hard to let your hair
down. You are in America now.

140
00:06:28,521 --> 00:06:31,685
You know, I don't know what
you're basing this on since...

141
00:06:32,692 --> 00:06:35,753
You know how hard it was
to find a jersey that small?

142
00:06:35,929 --> 00:06:37,659
- Hockey?
- See? I'm fun.

143
00:06:37,831 --> 00:06:39,800
We're gonna finish
then head to the rink.

144
00:06:39,966 --> 00:06:41,332
Oh, Neela, this is so hot.

145
00:06:41,501 --> 00:06:44,528
- Can you do a triple axel?
- Dude, that's figure skating.

146
00:06:44,771 --> 00:06:46,706
- Oh. GROSSMAN:
You friends with that guy?

147
00:06:46,907 --> 00:06:49,934
- Sort of.
- Oh, tell the truth. We slept together.

148
00:06:50,143 --> 00:06:52,476
She gave me a rash.

149
00:06:55,515 --> 00:06:57,950
- Hey, I'm sorry about the last few days.
- Oh, hey.

150
00:06:58,118 --> 00:07:01,714
I've been working 11 a.m. to 11
p.m., which is like falling off the planet.

151
00:07:01,922 --> 00:07:03,515
It's okay. I've
been slammed too.

152
00:07:03,690 --> 00:07:07,127
I'm leading a seminar at the
CAHC tomorrow and I'm way behind.

153
00:07:07,294 --> 00:07:08,785
What's CAHC?

154
00:07:08,962 --> 00:07:11,022
Complementary Alternative
Health Conference.

155
00:07:11,197 --> 00:07:12,995
- I told you all about it.
- You didn't.

156
00:07:13,166 --> 00:07:15,158
You may have been
in a post-coital stupor.

157
00:07:15,335 --> 00:07:19,568
But I am presenting data on
the effects of prayer on healing.

158
00:07:19,739 --> 00:07:22,402
- They actually have data on that?
- Yes. Ahem.

159
00:07:22,575 --> 00:07:26,410
Several studies have shown that patients
who have people praying for them...

160
00:07:26,579 --> 00:07:28,480
get well faster than
those who don't.

161
00:07:28,648 --> 00:07:31,015
- Ooh. Spooky.
- Shut up, the results are cool.

162
00:07:31,184 --> 00:07:33,676
When you get a minute, I
got a guy for you in Trauma.

163
00:07:33,853 --> 00:07:35,515
No, no, not another consult.

164
00:07:35,689 --> 00:07:37,988
I have to get this talk
together or I'm screwed.

165
00:07:38,158 --> 00:07:39,990
He saved a kid from
drowning in a lake.

166
00:07:40,160 --> 00:07:42,493
The kid's not doing so
well and he's freaked out.

167
00:07:42,662 --> 00:07:44,426
Come on, now.

168
00:07:44,597 --> 00:07:47,829
Okay. I have a baby-naming
ceremony in the NICU...

169
00:07:48,001 --> 00:07:50,869
and then I am meeting
with a statistician...

170
00:07:51,037 --> 00:07:53,768
to go over the
slides for the talk.

171
00:07:53,974 --> 00:07:56,102
I'll come back after that.
- Thank you.

172
00:07:56,276 --> 00:07:59,735
- Chest x-ray on Robert Truman.
- Good.

173
00:08:01,114 --> 00:08:03,242
- You're kidding me.
- Ugly, right?

174
00:08:03,416 --> 00:08:06,215
- Yeesh. Who's that?
- Old lake guy.

175
00:08:06,386 --> 00:08:09,379
Order a chest CT and I'll
get an official read on that.

176
00:08:09,589 --> 00:08:12,753
Tell me you don't need a
radiologist to see this film is abnormal.

177
00:08:12,926 --> 00:08:16,920
- Diffuse lung nodules, I know.
- Lung mets.

178
00:08:17,097 --> 00:08:19,589
I called you to get your
take on the differential...

179
00:08:19,766 --> 00:08:22,930
before I go in there and tell the
man he has metastatic cancer.

180
00:08:23,103 --> 00:08:28,201
Couldn't it be miliary TB or
cocci or sarcoid or something?

181
00:08:28,375 --> 00:08:33,109
Yeah, but in a 68-year-old
guy, odds are it's gonna be mets.

182
00:08:33,279 --> 00:08:36,306
- Great.
- So anything else?

183
00:08:38,718 --> 00:08:40,516
Guess not.

184
00:08:41,421 --> 00:08:43,720
Thanks for the consult.

185
00:08:48,161 --> 00:08:49,891
Dr. Truman.

186
00:08:50,063 --> 00:08:51,827
Robert, please.

187
00:08:52,032 --> 00:08:56,902
In your days as a prison doc, did
you ever get tested positive for TB?

188
00:08:57,070 --> 00:09:01,735
No, I had the PPD
every four months.

189
00:09:01,908 --> 00:09:05,310
Any coughing,
fevers, night sweats?

190
00:09:05,478 --> 00:09:08,778
Huh. The chest x-ray.

191
00:09:08,948 --> 00:09:11,110
Metastatic prostate cancer.

192
00:09:11,818 --> 00:09:16,051
It spread to my lungs and my
bones before I even knew I had it.

193
00:09:17,624 --> 00:09:22,494
- I'm sorry.
- Well, I guess it's my retribution.

194
00:09:23,129 --> 00:09:24,188
Excuse me?

195
00:09:25,465 --> 00:09:30,961
When men try to do God's
work, bad things happen.

196
00:09:31,971 --> 00:09:36,136
I wish I'd realized this
before I killed that boy's father.

197
00:09:38,778 --> 00:09:39,837
Another run of V-tach.

198
00:09:40,013 --> 00:09:42,278
Two hundred of bretylium
and start an infusion.

199
00:09:42,449 --> 00:09:44,816
- Core temp's down to 71.
- He's getting colder?

200
00:09:45,018 --> 00:09:46,543
Cold blood in his extremities...

201
00:09:46,719 --> 00:09:49,154
rushes up to his heart
and drops the core temp.

202
00:09:49,322 --> 00:09:51,382
Your Bair Hugger
worked a little too well.

203
00:09:51,591 --> 00:09:54,151
His heart can't beat
normally at this temperature.

204
00:09:54,327 --> 00:09:56,091
Sam, call the ECMO tech.

205
00:09:56,529 --> 00:09:59,863
Don't you think that's jumping the
gun? What about peritoneal lavage?

206
00:10:00,033 --> 00:10:02,502
- What's ECMO?
- Cardiac bypass.

207
00:10:02,669 --> 00:10:04,900
It's the only thing that's
gonna warm the core.

208
00:10:05,105 --> 00:10:06,698
It's too dangerous.

209
00:10:06,873 --> 00:10:09,240
His temperature is 71.
He's having runs of V-tach.

210
00:10:09,409 --> 00:10:11,002
- We're there.
- Bleeding, infection...

211
00:10:11,177 --> 00:10:12,737
- He knows the risks.
- Thank you.

212
00:10:12,912 --> 00:10:15,643
But I'm with Sam. Gabriel's
got a pulse and a decent BP.

213
00:10:15,815 --> 00:10:17,909
Exhaust all options
before jumping to ECMO.

214
00:10:18,151 --> 00:10:19,210
I'll get the stuff.

215
00:10:19,385 --> 00:10:22,981
Put a tube in belly and flush warm fluids
to see if we can raise his core temp.

216
00:10:23,156 --> 00:10:26,388
- Hey, Sam, what's with you today?
- Nothing.

217
00:10:26,559 --> 00:10:29,154
- Then why do you have to plan B me?
- Plan B you?

218
00:10:29,329 --> 00:10:31,161
Whatever I say, you
have a better idea.

219
00:10:31,331 --> 00:10:33,266
- That's not true.
- Yeah, Sam, it is true.

220
00:10:33,433 --> 00:10:36,267
Bair Hugger versus water
blanket. Morphine versus fentanyl.

221
00:10:36,436 --> 00:10:37,927
Okay, come on, you sound crazy.

222
00:10:38,138 --> 00:10:40,232
Whatever I want,
you give me that look.

223
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:42,602
- What look?
- That look, that one, right there.

224
00:10:42,775 --> 00:10:44,573
I don't accept orders
from someone...

225
00:10:44,744 --> 00:10:46,906
because they come
from a doctor or a man.

226
00:10:47,147 --> 00:10:49,548
I've been doing this a
lot longer than you have.

227
00:10:49,716 --> 00:10:53,209
If you don't like
that, it's too bad.

228
00:10:58,525 --> 00:11:01,723
Back at Stateville, my job
was to give lethal injections...

229
00:11:01,928 --> 00:11:04,227
to death-row inmates.

230
00:11:04,430 --> 00:11:07,992
- Wow, that's heavy.
- Yes.

231
00:11:09,035 --> 00:11:10,731
People could watch
through a window.

232
00:11:10,937 --> 00:11:13,566
