I remember her.

233
00:11:14,207 --> 00:11:20,511
Trying to be brave for the
baby as I injected the thiopental...

234
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:22,308
the Pavulon...

235
00:11:22,982 --> 00:11:25,042
potassium.

236
00:11:25,218 --> 00:11:27,687
Gabriel was only 2.

237
00:11:27,854 --> 00:11:30,153
He never knew his dad.

238
00:11:30,990 --> 00:11:33,482
Dr. Truman, you don't
really have to talk about this.

239
00:11:33,660 --> 00:11:35,720
No.

240
00:11:35,895 --> 00:11:39,332
Back then, I thought
it was the right thing.

241
00:11:39,499 --> 00:11:41,991
I thought there were
criminals who deserved to die...

242
00:11:42,168 --> 00:11:45,536
and lethal injection was
the most humane way.

243
00:11:45,705 --> 00:11:49,574
As time went on, my
thinking's changed.

244
00:11:49,742 --> 00:11:52,234
About the death penalty?

245
00:11:52,412 --> 00:11:58,249
Who lives and dies should
be decided by God, not a jury.

246
00:11:58,418 --> 00:12:00,046
I've spent the
last five years...

247
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:02,621
tracking the loved ones
of the men I've killed.

248
00:12:02,789 --> 00:12:06,021
Trying to make amends
with those families.

249
00:12:06,759 --> 00:12:09,388
And how do you make amends?

250
00:12:09,562 --> 00:12:13,693
Financial aid, mostly.
It's all I have to offer.

251
00:12:13,866 --> 00:12:18,634
I paid a mortgage, bought
a car, sent a child to college.

252
00:12:20,406 --> 00:12:23,570
Some people told me to get lost.

253
00:12:23,743 --> 00:12:26,872
Others took what I could offer.

254
00:12:27,947 --> 00:12:30,109
Well, that's really brave.

255
00:12:30,283 --> 00:12:33,617
- And generous.
- No.

256
00:12:33,786 --> 00:12:36,381
They're all acts of contrition.

257
00:12:36,556 --> 00:12:38,047
Small things.

258
00:12:38,891 --> 00:12:44,626
Nothing will ever bring back
a husband or a son, father.

259
00:12:45,832 --> 00:12:48,392
Saving a kid's life
isn't a small thing.

260
00:12:49,736 --> 00:12:54,071
I'm just trying to tell God how
sorry I am for what I've done.

261
00:12:54,240 --> 00:12:56,607
Please.

262
00:12:56,776 --> 00:13:00,144
I need that boy to live.

263
00:13:04,684 --> 00:13:06,516
Tell that freak to
stop staring at me.

264
00:13:06,686 --> 00:13:09,485
Not many people would jump
in a frozen lake for a stranger.

265
00:13:09,656 --> 00:13:12,922
- He's not a stranger, he's a stalker.
- V-tach, lost the pulse.

266
00:13:13,126 --> 00:13:16,096
- Starting compressions.
- Oh, my God. What's happening?

267
00:13:16,262 --> 00:13:18,288
His heart has stopped
beating effectively.

268
00:13:18,464 --> 00:13:20,524
We can't shock it
back until he's warmer.

269
00:13:20,700 --> 00:13:23,465
This looks like the right room.
- Who called for ECMO?

270
00:13:23,636 --> 00:13:26,697
The conservative route wouldn't
work so I gave Teddy the heads-up.

271
00:13:26,873 --> 00:13:29,809
Put him on. This is a
cardiopulmonary bypass machine.

272
00:13:29,976 --> 00:13:32,445
It will function as
