pleading, praying.

346
00:18:01,414 --> 00:18:06,614
I injected the drugs
and he didn't die.

347
00:18:07,420 --> 00:18:10,948
He lay there, awake, quivering.

348
00:18:11,123 --> 00:18:14,958
Lethal doses of three different
agents and he was still alive.

349
00:18:15,127 --> 00:18:18,427
Parents were crying,
claiming a miracle.

350
00:18:18,965 --> 00:18:23,266
- What happened?
- The IV infiltrated.

351
00:18:23,803 --> 00:18:29,470
The drugs pooled in his soft tissues
instead of going into his bloodstream.

352
00:18:29,642 --> 00:18:36,014
So I placed another IV, drew up
another round of meds and pushed.

353
00:18:36,916 --> 00:18:39,010
And this time...

354
00:18:40,319 --> 00:18:42,584
it took him 90 seconds to die.

355
00:18:45,658 --> 00:18:49,254
Seven months later, a
police officer came forward.

356
00:18:50,529 --> 00:18:54,489
The boy was framed
for the murder. Hm?

357
00:18:55,935 --> 00:18:57,699
He didn't do it.

358
00:18:59,939 --> 00:19:01,339
You couldn't have known that.

359
00:19:03,042 --> 00:19:05,534
God tried to stop me from
killing an innocent man...

360
00:19:05,711 --> 00:19:07,680
and I ignored the sign.

361
00:19:07,847 --> 00:19:10,783
How can I even
hope for forgiveness?

362
00:19:11,684 --> 00:19:13,846
I think...

363
00:19:14,020 --> 00:19:18,981
sometimes it's easier to
feel guilty than forgiven.

364
00:19:23,863 --> 00:19:25,058
Which means what?

365
00:19:26,298 --> 00:19:31,737
That maybe your guilt over these
deaths has become your reason for living.

366
00:19:31,937 --> 00:19:35,339
Maybe you need a
new reason to go on.

367
00:19:35,508 --> 00:19:38,068
I don't want to go on.

368
00:19:38,244 --> 00:19:43,581
Can't you see I'm old? I
have cancer. I've had enough.

369
00:19:43,749 --> 00:19:46,878
The only thing that is holding
me back is that I am afraid.

370
00:19:47,053 --> 00:19:51,388
- I'm afraid of what comes next.
- And what do you think that is?

371
00:19:51,590 --> 00:19:53,650
Oh, you tell me.

372
00:19:53,826 --> 00:19:57,194
Is atonement even possible?
What does God want from me?

373
00:19:57,363 --> 00:20:01,198
I think it's up to each one of
us to interpret what God wants.

374
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:03,892
So people can do anything?

375
00:20:04,070 --> 00:20:07,700
They can rape, murder, steal, all
in the name of God and it's okay?

376
00:20:07,873 --> 00:20:10,502
- No, that's not what I'm saying.
- What are you saying?

377
00:20:10,676 --> 00:20:17,515
