- No, I don't have time for this now.

379
00:20:21,554 --> 00:20:23,546
Greg, it's okay.

380
00:20:23,723 --> 00:20:26,124
- Look, I understand...
- No, you don't understand.

381
00:20:26,292 --> 00:20:28,284
You don't understand.

382
00:20:28,494 --> 00:20:31,396
How could you possibly say
that? Now, you listen to me.

383
00:20:32,064 --> 00:20:35,899
I want a real chaplain who
believes in a real God and a real hell.

384
00:20:36,535 --> 00:20:39,027
You're frustrated, but
you need to ask yourself...

385
00:20:39,205 --> 00:20:43,870
No, I don't need to ask
myself. I need answers.

386
00:20:44,043 --> 00:20:47,480
And all your questions
and your uncertainty...

387
00:20:47,646 --> 00:20:50,047
are only making things worse.

388
00:20:52,451 --> 00:20:54,647
- I know you're upset.
- God.

389
00:20:54,887 --> 00:20:57,482
I need someone who
will look me in the eye...

390
00:20:57,656 --> 00:21:02,754
and tell me how to find forgiveness
because I am running out of time.

391
00:21:05,331 --> 00:21:08,301
- I'm trying to help.
- Well, don't. Just get out.

392
00:21:09,101 --> 00:21:11,536
Get out! Get out!

393
00:21:15,307 --> 00:21:18,800
Hey, Julia. Julia, come
on. Listen, come on.

394
00:21:19,044 --> 00:21:22,572
Come on, the guy's just freaking
out. He didn't mean what he said.

