00:26:49,441 --> 00:26:51,603
I guess he's had a change
of heart. Excuse me.

471
00:26:51,777 --> 00:26:54,508
Hey, Chaz, hey. Hey, man.

472
00:26:57,749 --> 00:26:59,081
Hey, Celia.

473
00:27:01,420 --> 00:27:05,118
- Everything all right?
- Yeah.

474
00:27:05,290 --> 00:27:07,759
Yeah, it's just work, you know?

475
00:27:14,433 --> 00:27:17,335
I guess she wants a
commitment, but I don't know.

476
00:27:17,503 --> 00:27:19,472
Maybe I'm not that kind of guy.

477
00:27:19,638 --> 00:27:21,504
So why don't you
just tell her that?

478
00:27:21,673 --> 00:27:22,766
Bettina's great.

479
00:27:22,941 --> 00:27:25,172
It's not like I'm looking
for something better.

480
00:27:25,344 --> 00:27:27,108
You been together
for a while now.

481
00:27:27,279 --> 00:27:29,680
- Yeah, nine months.
- Hm!

482
00:27:29,848 --> 00:27:31,441
That must be a record for you.

483
00:27:31,617 --> 00:27:34,451
I like her, all right?
So that's not the issue.

484
00:27:34,620 --> 00:27:37,613
Well, why don't you just give
it a try and see what happens?

485
00:27:37,789 --> 00:27:38,984
It's easy for you to say.

486
00:27:39,158 --> 00:27:41,992
You're 20 years old
and still playing the field.

487
00:27:42,161 --> 00:27:44,858
Greg, I've been with the
same guy for almost a year now.

488
00:27:45,063 --> 00:27:47,157
Really? Why didn't
you tell me that before?

489
00:27:49,134 --> 00:27:51,968
- You never asked.
- All right, well, I should take these.

490
00:27:52,137 --> 00:27:54,333
- Cool, thanks for the coffee.
- Oh, anytime.

491
00:27:54,506 --> 00:27:55,997
Hey, what's his name?

492
00:27:56,208 --> 00:27:58,473
- Andrew.
- Well, I'd like to meet him sometime.

493
00:27:58,677 --> 00:28:01,078
We can all go to a
drag club or something.

494
00:28:01,313 --> 00:28:04,306
Ha! Just kidding,
man. That'd be cool.

495
00:28:04,483 --> 00:28:05,542
What you got?

496
00:28:05,717 --> 00:28:08,312
Mass cas at the ice rink.
Ortho versus Trauma.

497
00:28:08,487 --> 00:28:10,547
What? CRENSHAW: You.

498
00:28:10,789 --> 00:28:12,485
You were a complete
goon out there.

499
00:28:12,691 --> 00:28:15,217
- I hit you because you elbowed me.
- Headhunter.

500
00:28:15,394 --> 00:28:16,726
- Octopus - Slasher.

501
00:28:16,929 --> 00:28:19,807
- Can't we all just get along?
- Rasgotra, this isn't over.

502
00:28:19,831 --> 00:28:22,266
I saved your ass so
many times out there.

503
00:28:24,203 --> 00:28:27,105
Well, maybe I wouldn't have
to if you weren't such a goon.

504
00:28:27,306 --> 00:28:29,002
You should
practice a little more.

505
00:28:29,208 --> 00:28:31,439
You've had plenty of
practice swinging stick.

506
00:28:31,677 --> 00:28:34,306
Could you lay down? I don't
recognize you standing up.

507
00:28:40,852 --> 00:28:43,412
Hey, get off of him, you wanker.

508
00:28:44,189 --> 00:28:48,854
The ECMO tech needs you in
T-2 right away. That kid's awake.

509
00:28:51,129 --> 00:28:52,324
Cripes!

510
00:28:53,732 --> 00:28:54,791
What's going on?

511
00:28:54,967 --> 00:28:58,597
We see this after a few hours on
the machine. They just wake up.

512
00:28:59,605 --> 00:29:01,972
Sat's okay on room air.

513
00:29:02,574 --> 00:29:04,770
Mommy? What happened?

514
00:29:04,977 --> 00:29:06,639
Oh, baby.

515
00:29:06,845 --> 00:29:09,872
Hi, baby, hi. You're okay.

516
00:29:10,082 --> 00:29:12,415
- Attaboy, Gabriel.
- Oh, thank God.

517
00:29:12,618 --> 00:29:15,588
- He's okay. He's gonna be okay.
- I know, baby.

518
00:29:15,754 --> 00:29:17,450
Core temp's up to 94.

519
00:29:17,623 --> 00:29:20,718
This family will never forget
what you did here today.

520
00:29:20,926 --> 00:29:22,087
Just doing our job.

521
00:29:22,294 --> 00:29:25,162
Well, I don't care what
you say. It's a miracle.

522
00:29:25,764 --> 00:29:28,097
What do you say we take
this kid off the machine?

523
00:29:28,267 --> 00:29:30,429
- Sounds good.
- Size 8 gloves okay?

524
00:29:30,602 --> 00:29:33,162
Looks like good news in there.

525
00:29:35,107 --> 00:29:36,803
This doesn't absolve you.

526
00:29:38,810 --> 00:29:40,870
Don't think it does.

527
00:29:42,247 --> 00:29:44,443
I don't forgive you.

528
00:29:44,616 --> 00:29:46,915
I will never forgive you.

529
00:29:49,755 --> 00:29:52,919
You have to live with
what you've done.

530
00:30:16,181 --> 00:30:17,979
Julia.

531
00:30:19,751 --> 00:30:22,516
Well, the lake
kid is doing great.

532
00:30:23,588 --> 00:30:25,580
But our guy...

533
00:30:26,658 --> 00:30:28,991
He needs you in there.

534
00:30:29,961 --> 00:30:31,759
I can't.

535
00:30:33,231 --> 00:30:35,826
All right, well, I
need you in there.

536
00:30:36,001 --> 00:30:39,961
He's asking me all kind of questions
that I don't know how to answer.

537
00:30:42,274 --> 00:30:49,037
You know, doubt...
it's uncomfortable.

538
00:30:49,214 --> 00:30:51,877
But certainty...

539
00:30:53,385 --> 00:30:55,251
I don't think it's real.

540
00:30:57,255 --> 00:30:59,520
I mean, I went to seminary.

541
00:31:00,092 --> 00:31:05,429
I studied Buddhism, I
spent time at an ashram.

542
00:31:07,199 --> 00:31:11,534
Who really knows anything
with absolute certainty?

543
00:31:11,703 --> 00:31:14,901
Not me, that's for sure.

544
00:31:15,073 --> 00:31:17,975
That's why I thought an
inclusive approach to spirituality...

545
00:31:18,143 --> 00:31:20,112
would work well
in a place like this.

546
00:31:20,278 --> 00:31:21,803
It does. It does.

547
00:31:22,013 --> 00:31:24,005
The patients, they
appreciate what you do.

548
00:31:24,216 --> 00:31:28,381
No, people in crisis want
rules. They want structure.

549
00:31:28,553 --> 00:31:31,546
Something to
lean on, I get that.

550
00:31:32,391 --> 00:31:33,791
But it's not me.

551
00:31:35,660 --> 00:31:39,392
You know, we all wonder what
we're doing here sometimes.

552
00:31:41,266 --> 00:31:42,427
That guy needs help.

553
00:31:44,636 --> 00:31:46,468
So come on.

554
00:31:46,638 --> 00:31:50,075
Come back in there with
me. Let's go talk to him.

555
00:31:52,911 --> 00:31:55,039
I don't think so.

556
00:32:01,620 --> 00:32:03,179
All right.

557
00:32:07,859 --> 00:32:09,760
Ramsey, did you
trip over the blue line?

558
00:32:09,928 --> 00:32:11,487
Yeah, fell on me.

559
00:32:11,663 --> 00:32:14,678
Morris, hurt yourself
doing a triple axel?

560
00:32:14,702 --> 00:32:15,702
So who won?

561
00:32:15,767 --> 00:32:17,360
It was a mutual forfeit.

562
00:32:17,569 --> 00:32:20,038
- Didn't know you had it in you, Mayday.
- Me neither.

563
00:32:20,205 --> 00:32:23,198
- X-ray's negative, home with splint.
- All right, who's next?

564
00:32:23,375 --> 00:32:25,674
Hey, Neela, how's your boo-boo?

565
00:32:25,877 --> 00:32:27,607
It's my dominant hand.

566
00:32:27,779 --> 00:32:30,010
- If I can't operate, you're dead.
- Wuss.

567
00:32:30,182 --> 00:32:31,262
You hack.

568
00:32:31,383 --> 00:32:32,476
Beyotch.

569
00:32:32,651 --> 00:32:35,553
- Who are you yelling at, Harold?
- I don't really know.

570
00:32:35,720 --> 00:32:39,623
- No tenderness, bearing weight.
- Hey, how's my team?

571
00:32:39,791 --> 00:32:42,351
They need ibuprofen, a
hot tub and a glass of wine.

572
00:32:42,527 --> 00:32:45,691
- I like the way you think.
- Okay, listen up, everyone, fun's over.

573
00:32:45,864 --> 00:32:47,833
Orthopods are rounding
on the hall in 10.

574
00:32:47,999 --> 00:32:49,865
- Trauma to the ICU.
- What about me?

575
00:32:50,035 --> 00:32:53,528
There's an ingrown toenail in
Exam 3 with your name on it.

576
00:32:53,705 --> 00:32:57,005
Sam. What's up, buddy,
you sick of us down here?

577
00:32:57,209 --> 00:32:58,609
No, I like it.

578
00:32:58,810 --> 00:33:02,406
- You like it? You're a weird kid.
- He likes the Jell-O.

579
00:33:02,614 --> 00:33:03,809
Thanks again, doctor.

580
00:33:04,015 --> 00:33:06,575
You're welcome. You take
care of your mom, okay?

581
00:33:06,751 --> 00:33:07,912
Sam, any beds open up?

582
00:33:08,119 --> 00:33:11,248
Well, I had to threaten the
charge nurse with physical violence.

583
00:33:11,423 --> 00:33:12,584
But something opened up.

584
00:33:12,757 --> 00:33:15,386
All right, we're going to Ike
Ryan's. You should come.

585
00:33:15,627 --> 00:33:16,686
- Should I?
- Yeah.

586
00:33:16,862 --> 00:33:20,731
As long as if I order you a beer,
you don't change it to vodka gimlet.

587
00:33:20,899 --> 00:33:24,097
I don't know. I have to report
upstairs. I gotta do stuff here.

588
00:33:24,269 --> 00:33:26,238
How often do we get
an outcome like this?

589
00:33:26,404 --> 00:33:28,106
A pulseless ice
cube turned into a

590
00:33:28,130 --> 00:33:30,364
Jell-O-loving 11-year-old
in the same shift.

591
00:33:30,575 --> 00:33:34,171
- That doesn't happen every day.
- That's for sure.

592
00:33:34,646 --> 00:33:39,516
- Well?
- Well, I'll see if I can make it.

593
00:34:32,137 --> 00:34:34,402
<i>I have sinned against heaven.</i>

594
00:34:37,275 --> 00:34:42,441
And in your sight
are no more worthy.

595
00:34:44,616 --> 00:34:46,642
Gracious God.

596
00:34:49,354 --> 00:34:54,486
My mortal sentence I accept.

597
00:34:57,996 --> 00:34:59,794
Stop.

598
00:34:59,998 --> 00:35:03,628
- What the hell are you doing?
- I am in hell.

599
00:35:03,802 --> 00:35:07,466
Do you understand? I am in
hell already. I might as well go.

600
00:35:07,672 --> 00:35:10,836
Listen to me. You
saved a little boy's life.

601
00:35:11,042 --> 00:35:13,773
No, it is not enough. I
can't change my destiny.

602
00:35:13,945 --> 00:35:15,345
There isn't time.

603
00:35:15,547 --> 00:35:17,709
Did it ever occur to
you that your destiny...

604
00:35:17,882 --> 00:35:20,511
was for you to be on
that pier this morning?

605
00:35:20,685 --> 00:35:23,780
That maybe your life's path and
all the choices that you made...

606
00:35:23,955 --> 00:35:25,048
led you right there.

607
00:35:25,256 --> 00:35:26,815
- Why?
- So you could save that kid.

608
00:35:26,992 --> 00:35:29,052
Why? Why would God do that?

609
00:35:29,260 --> 00:35:33,197
Why would he have me
kill 17 people to save one?

610
00:35:33,398 --> 00:35:34,730
You may not understand it...

611
00:35:34,899 --> 00:35:37,562
but that little boy is alive
because you were there.

612
00:35:38,136 --> 00:35:42,198
Now, whatever you need
that to count for, it counts.

613
00:35:50,415 --> 00:35:52,884
It doesn't make sense.

614
00:35:55,920 --> 00:35:58,788
It doesn't have to make sense.

615
00:36:00,425 --> 00:36:02,985
That's why it's called faith.

616
00:36:23,715 --> 00:36:25,445
All right.

617
00:36:28,720 --> 00:36:31,417
- Hey, guys.
- Hey, Sam, great job today.

618
00:36:31,589 --> 00:36:34,388
- Thank you, you too.
- Hey, Gabriel all tucked in?

619
00:36:34,559 --> 00:36:38,428
Yes. The ICU nurses
are fawning all over him.

620
00:36:38,630 --> 00:36:41,065
- My turn to win some money.
- All right.

621
00:36:41,566 --> 00:36:45,196
- So, what are you drinking?
- Actually, I can't stay.

622
00:36:45,403 --> 00:36:48,100
So you came here to tell
me that you can't come here?

623
00:36:48,773 --> 00:36:50,401
- Yeah.
- Really?

624
00:36:50,575 --> 00:36:52,737
Have you heard
of the cell phone?

625
00:36:52,911 --> 00:36:57,246
You know what, you're right. It's dumb.
I shouldn't have come. I wasn't thinking.

626
00:36:57,415 --> 00:37:00,408
Wow, she admits that she
wasn't thinking. Alert the media.

627
00:37:01,152 --> 00:37:03,485
- Screw you, Gates.
- Come on, stay here.

628
00:37:03,655 --> 00:37:06,716
Will you get her a beer, please?
- You got it.

629
00:37:07,459 --> 00:37:10,588
Vodka gimlet with a twist.
- Okay.

630
00:37:13,665 --> 00:37:18,626
Definitely the most insane shift
I've worked since I started here.

631
00:37:18,803 --> 00:37:21,602
You said that exact
same thing yesterday.

632
00:37:21,773 --> 00:37:23,469
I did not.

633
00:37:25,376 --> 00:37:28,778
So are you going
to Ike's after this?

634
00:37:28,947 --> 00:37:31,678
No, I'm not much
of a group person.

635
00:37:31,883 --> 00:37:34,819
I need my alone time
at the end of the day.

636
00:37:35,653 --> 00:37:38,020
Is that why you're not married?

637
00:37:40,125 --> 00:37:41,593
No.

638
00:37:42,594 --> 00:37:48,124
Then why isn't a hot, smart woman
such as yourself shacked up by now?

639
00:37:49,901 --> 00:37:51,995
And I'm not hitting on you.

640
00:37:52,170 --> 00:37:55,629
Just wondering if some people
aren't cut out for commitment.

641
00:37:57,776 --> 00:37:59,404
Nobody's cut out for commitment.

642
00:38:00,812 --> 00:38:02,110
It fights our DNA.

643
00:38:03,515 --> 00:38:07,611
- You don't believe in monogamy?
- No, I believe in monogamy.

644
00:38:07,786 --> 00:38:12,019
I just don't believe in
the concept of forever.

645
00:38:12,991 --> 00:38:16,985
People force the issue and then
act surprised when it doesn't work out.

646
00:38:18,163 --> 00:38:21,065
You know, some people
might say that your theory...

647
00:38:21,232 --> 00:38:23,861
is a cover for a
fear of commitment.

648
00:38:27,172 --> 00:38:30,301
Well, it takes a lot
of courage to reject...

649
00:38:30,475 --> 00:38:33,343
the widely embraced
social construct of marriage.

650
00:38:34,078 --> 00:38:37,344
Most people assume you've
got some kind of problem.

651
00:38:41,986 --> 00:38:45,252
Well, seems like you've
got it all figured out.

652
00:38:46,825 --> 00:38:48,157
Some days.

653
00:38:54,499 --> 00:38:57,992
- Night, Skye.
- Night.

654
00:39:00,672 --> 00:39:02,231
How'd you hurt your shoulder?

655
00:39:02,407 --> 00:39:08,278
Checked by Grossman after the
face-off. But I hurt him worse later.

656
00:39:09,881 --> 00:39:12,908
Ever seen bonobos at the zoo?

657
00:39:13,084 --> 00:39:15,417
What's a bonobo?

658
00:39:15,587 --> 00:39:17,715
Pygmy chimp.

659
00:39:18,356 --> 00:39:23,522
Famous in the primate world
for their social-sexual behavior.

660
00:39:24,362 --> 00:39:26,888
How fascinating.

661
00:39:32,804 --> 00:39:34,568
In bonobo communities...

662
00:39:35,540 --> 00:39:37,634
sex is a way to say hello.

663
00:39:38,276 --> 00:39:40,268
- Oh, really?
- Mm-hm.

664
00:39:40,445 --> 00:39:42,209
Hello.

665
00:39:43,114 --> 00:39:46,084
- This is so awesome. NEELA:
I didn't know these were here.

666
00:39:46,251 --> 00:39:49,449
Hot tubs are for therapy
during the day, but night?

667
00:39:49,621 --> 00:39:52,216
They belong to the hockey team.

668
00:39:52,390 --> 00:39:54,757
Lucien, Skye, how's the water?

669
00:39:56,160 --> 00:39:58,459
Hot, very hot.

670
00:40:05,837 --> 00:40:08,932
Guys, this job rocks.

671
00:40:12,310 --> 00:40:14,575
I'm not sure what the
point of that would be...

672
00:40:14,746 --> 00:40:18,342
other than to make him feel
guilty on top of everything else.

673
00:40:18,549 --> 00:40:22,816
Uh, I gotta go. Okay, bye.

674
00:40:22,987 --> 00:40:25,582
- Hey.
- Hey.

675
00:40:25,757 --> 00:40:27,555
What's up?

676
00:40:29,427 --> 00:40:30,918
We need to talk.

677
00:40:34,332 --> 00:40:39,202
I'm sorry about this morning,
okay? You had the right to be mad.

678
00:40:39,370 --> 00:40:41,703
Apology accepted.

679
00:40:43,574 --> 00:40:45,099
Look...

680
00:40:46,778 --> 00:40:50,374
This is all new to me, okay?

681
00:40:50,581 --> 00:40:52,709
I haven't been down
this path before.

682
00:40:54,285 --> 00:40:57,881
But I really, really
want this to work.

683
00:41:00,792 --> 00:41:05,287
Do you know if you stare at an
x-ray for more than 38 seconds...

684
00:41:05,463 --> 00:41:07,694
you start to see
things that aren't there?

685
00:41:08,166 --> 00:41:09,896
Because that's
what's this is, Greg.

686
00:41:10,101 --> 00:41:12,161
We've stared at
this thing too long...

687
00:41:12,337 --> 00:41:15,671
and tricked ourselves into
seeing something that isn't there.

688
00:41:15,840 --> 00:41:18,639
You're not listening,
okay? I wanna do this.

689
00:41:18,843 --> 00:41:21,540
This morning, you
seemed totally unsure.

690
00:41:21,713 --> 00:41:23,306
Who's sure about anything?

691
00:41:23,481 --> 00:41:25,347
This shouldn't
have to be this hard.

692
00:41:26,017 --> 00:41:30,182
Eventually you know we would
end up right back in the same place.

693
00:41:31,489 --> 00:41:35,017
And frankly, I
don't have the time.

694
00:41:47,538 --> 00:41:50,770
- Thank you for waiting with me.
- No problem.

695
00:41:51,442 --> 00:41:52,842
Oh.

696
00:41:53,745 --> 00:41:55,771
ECMO was a good
call with that kid.

697
00:41:56,014 --> 00:41:58,779
We probably should
have done it sooner.

698
00:41:58,950 --> 00:42:00,919
It's annoying but
you were right.

699
00:42:01,152 --> 00:42:02,211
Thank you.

700
00:42:02,387 --> 00:42:05,653
And, Sam, I do like
working with you.

701
00:42:06,524 --> 00:42:09,517
Other than the relentless
interrogation and second-guessing...

702
00:42:09,694 --> 00:42:11,526
and you constantly
blowing me off...

703
00:42:11,696 --> 00:42:14,188
- Shut up.
- When I give you orders.

704
00:42:21,806 --> 00:42:23,775
I hate you.

705
00:42:25,076 --> 00:42:26,305
I hate you too.
